commit.message:
Tweaked the definition of bounded-integer-alistp2.  Use set-table-guard to improve error messages for add-invisible-fns.

Quoting :DOC note-8-6:

  Built-in function bounded-integer-alistp2 has been modified to remove
  [integerp] tests on formals i and j from the body and instead
  require them to satisfy [posp] in the [guard].

Thanks to Eric Smith for pointing out that the add-invisible-fns error
message could be a bit inscrutable.  For example, the last sentence
below is new.

ACL2 !>(add-invisible-fns binary-+ binary-*)

ACL2 Error in ( TABLE INVISIBLE-FNS-TABLE ...):  The TABLE :guard for
INVISIBLE-FNS-TABLE disallows the combination of key BINARY-+ and value
(BINARY-* UNARY--).  The :guard requires
(INVISIBLE-FNS-ENTRYP KEY VAL WORLD).  See :DOC INVISIBLE-FNS-TABLE.
Note that the test for INVISIBLE-FNS-ENTRYP has failed because BINARY-*
is not a known unary function symbol.
Fixed a slight performance bug in *1* functions, and improved some comments, pertaining to invariant-risk.  Deal with remainingx references in source code comments to big-clock.

Slightly strengthened type-reasoning and hence forward-chaining.

  The ACL2 [type-reasoning] mechanism has been strengthened slightly
  for an if expression being assumed true or false, when that
  expression has a subterm of the form (equal term 'c), or (equal 'c
  term) and c is 0, 1, t, or nil.  Thanks to Warren Hunt for sending
  an example involving [forward-chaining] that led to this
  improvement.  IMPORTANT NOTE: If this change causes a proof to fail
  that formerly succeeded, you can fix it by preceding it with the
  following (implicitly [local]) event.

    (defattach-system use-enhanced-recognizer constant-nil-function-arity-0)

The "IMPORTANT NOTE" above is illustrated by what I did to fix a proof
failure from
books/kestrel/crypto/r1cs/sparse/gadgets/range-check.lisp.  (Lemma
make-range-check-pi-constraints-correct-1-forward has 15 hypotheses, a
:cases hint, and a :use hint, and the failure was in the forcing round
and seemed difficult for me to fix.)  Here's the fix I made.

; Matt K. mod to accommodate change to strong-recognizer-expr-p in ACL2 near
; the end of March 2024.  Note that this event is local to this book.
(defattach-system acl2::use-enhanced-recognizer
  acl2::constant-nil-function-arity-0)

Technical note about the implementation: The strengthening is in
source function strong-recognizer-expr-p.

Fixed some issues with xdoc font displays at the terminal. I added the following two tests in books/system/doc/acl2-doc.lisp, included here since the first one's comments explain the issue. (defxdoc doc-terminal-test-1 ; An earlier version of :DOC displayed the :long section of this topic with the ; bold (red) test ending after EQUAL. That was because the SGR terminator (see ; *sgr-suffix* in books/xdoc/display.lisp) was terminating not only the ; typewriter font for EQUAL but also the bold font. Now, when EQUAL ends, ; function merge-text (see books/xdoc/display.lisp) restarts the stack of font ; changes other than the one currently being concluded. :parents (documentation) :short "Short" :long "

Symbol @('EQUAL') and the rest is still bold.

") (defxdoc doc-terminal-test-2 ; See comments in doc-terminal-test-1. Here, the fixed version of :DOC ; sometimes has difficulty displaying the fonts properly at the terminal, but ; they are fine when viewed with acl2-doc. :parents (documentation) :short "Short" :long "

Start underline Start bold Start italics TYPEWRITER FONT [WHICH ENDS HERE] Bold italics underlined Bold underlined. Underlined Normal text

")

Allow parent stobj in producer of a stobj-let when no producer variable is bound in the bindings.  Tweaked some scripts.  Improved a stobj-let error message.  Improved comments in the-fn and find-stobj-out-and-call.  Improved macroexpand1*-cmp.  Improved :DOC nested-stobjs to mention the "It is forbidden" message from using a variable illegally in a stobj-let producer or consumer.

  It is now legal for the parent stobj of a [stobj-let] expression to
  occur free in the producer when no producer variable is bound in
  the bindings.  For an example, see the section ``Allow the parent
  stobj of a stobj-let expression to occur free in the producer when
  no variable bound in the bindings occurs in the producer.'' in
  [community-book] books/system/tests/nested-stobj-tests.lisp.

My notes say that the script improvements are due to comments on Zulip
from Eric Smith.  Thanks, Eric.

Quoting comments in (defxdoc note-8-6 ...):

; Improved the error message in some cases when stobj-let binds a variable that
; is illegally used in the consumer.

; Technical change, only user visible in exceptional circumstances: fixed
; macroexpand1*-cmp to avoid macroexpansion in cases where translate11 could
; cause an error.
[axe/x86] Don't require types on :inputs to be keywords.
[axe/x86] Add new simd functions to rule-lists.

[axe/x86] Improve unroller.

For an array input, introduce vars for the elements.  Also improve param order in generated functions.
[axe/x86] Build in control register assumptions more deeply.
[axe] Have provers print more info upon failure.
[axe] Add util to print info about dags in array form.
